HEADWORD: Cousinry
<hw>Cous"in*ry</hw> <pr>(k?z"'n-r?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A body or collection of cousins; the whole number of persons who stand in the relation of cousins to a given person or persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

